It's not so bad.Start with the Kana, most people learn them both in a weekend. It's okay if it takes you longer, print out a chart.Learning the Kanji isn't the struggle to memorize the meaning of 3,000+ characters. It's about being able to read and figure out what each new Kanji means using its radicals as context to understand them.Download a Jsho on your phone and learn the radicals.It's not so bad. I started studying it after I gave up on my drunk Italian sounding French.È†ëÂºµ„Å£„Å¶!
